<pre><code>#include&lt;stdio.h&gt; #include&lt;stdlib.h&gt; #include&lt;malloc.h&gt;  struct node {     int id;     struct node *next; }; typedef struct node NODE; int main() {     NODE *hi;        printf("\nbefore malloc\n");     printf("\naddress of node is: %p",hi);     printf("\naddress of next is: %p",hi-&gt;next); return 0; } </code></pre>  <p>The output is:</p>  <p>before malloc</p>  <p>address of node is: 0x7ffd37e99e90 address of next is: 0x7ffd37e9a470</p>  <p>Why both are not same?</p>